				padding: 10rem 0 0 0;
			}
			.padding-top-20 {
				padding: 7rem 0 0 0;
			}
			.int-design {
				margin-top: 30rem
			}
			header {
				padding: 6.5rem 10vw;
			}
		}
	</style>
	
	<header>
		<nav>
			<a href="/" class="bold-900" style="text-decoration-color: #4c4c4f; color: #a1a1a6 !important;">Dillon J. Brown</a>
			<a href="mailto:hello@dillonbrown.me" style="text-decoration-color: #4c4c4f; color: #a1a1a6 !important;">Contact</a>
			<a href="resume.pdf" style="text-decoration-color: #4c4c4f; color: #a1a1a6 !important;">Résumé</a>
		</nav>
	</header>
	
	<!--
		MOBILE AUDIO APPS
	-->
	<section>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="six columns">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-mobile-audio-ui.svg -->
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="six offset-by-six columns">
				<p style="font-size: 1.7rem; color: #a1a1a6; margin-top: 4rem;">There are more music apps than ever. However, few of them are made for people like me. Instead of renting music from Spotify, I buy my own copy from sites like Bandcamp. Additionally, I have other kinds of audio files, like audiobooks, stand-up comedy albums, and longform podcasts no longer in a feed.</p>
				<p style="font-size: 1.7rem; color: #a1a1a6;">I want to make a suite of apps laser-focused on one medium each. These apps will share a codebase and similar interfaces, each fine-tuned to their content.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #a1a1a6; padding: 10rem 0;">
			<div class="three columns">
				<strong style="text-transform: uppercase; color: #F5F5F7;">Expertise</strong>
				<br>
				Design and Interaction
				<p></p>
			</div>
			<div class="three columns">
				<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;color: #F5F5F7;">Deliverables</strong>
				<br>
				UI, UX, and Pixel-Perfect Mockups
				<p></p>
			</div>
			<div class="three columns">
				<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;color: #F5F5F7;">Platform</strong>
				<br>
				iOS
				<p></p>
			</div>
			<div class="three columns">
				<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;color: #F5F5F7;">Check it out</strong>
				<br>
				↓
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<!--
		INTRO
	-->
	<div class="row" style="background: #fff; padding: 7rem 0 0 0;">
		<section>
			<div class="twelve columns">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/intro.png" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	<div class="row" style="background: #fff; padding: 0 0 7rem 0;">
		<section>
			<div class="three columns">
				<p style="color: black; font-weight: 700;">Music<br><span style="color: #989898;">iPhone SE</span></p>
				
			</div>
			<div class="three columns">
				<p style="color: black; font-weight: 700;">Podcasts<br><span style="color: #989898;">iPhone 8</span></p>
			</div>
			<div class="three columns">
				<p style="color: black; font-weight: 700;">Comedy<br><span style="color: #989898;">iPhone X</span></p>
			</div>
			<div class="three columns">
				<p style="color: black; font-weight: 700;">Audiobooks<br><span style="color: #989898;" class="center">iPhone 11 Pro Max</span></p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	
	<!--
		TOUCH TARGETS
	-->
	<div class="row" style="background: #EFEFF4; padding: 0 0 5rem 0;box-shadow: inset 0 9px 30px -10px rgba(217,217,217,1);;">
		<section>
			<div class="ten offset-by-one columns">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/phone-scrubber.png" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
			</div>
			<div class="ten offset-by-one columns center">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-lets-talk.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #161616;">My design introduces a large, finger-friendly scrubber. Grab the waveform from any location and slide horizontally to change your place in a song.</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	<div class="row" style="background: #EFEFF4; padding: 0 0 5rem 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
		<section>
			<div class="six columns center">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_touch-targets.svg -->
				<p style="color: #161616;">A large touch target makes for easy one-handed use with any grip.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="six columns center">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_touch-targets-2.svg -->
				<p style="color: #161616;"><a class="blue-link" href="https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/ios/visual-design/adaptivity-and-layout/">Apple's Human Interface Guidelines</a> suggest a minimum size of 44pt for interactive elements. Most popular apps don't even come close.</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	
	<!--
		BIG OL' BUTTONS
	-->
	<div class="row" style="background: #F5F5F7; color: #161616">
		<section>
			<div class="six columns padding-top-20">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-words.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem;margin-bottom: 15rem;">I have trouble divining the meaning of the endless glyphs on my phone. Words communicate actions more clearly.</p>
				
				<!-- If a picture is worth a thousand words, a glyph is worth none. -->
				
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-big-buttons.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem;">Need even bigger buttons? My design gives you an option to replace playback controls with gestures and a mega play/pause button.
				<p style="font-size: 2rem;">Tap on the artwork to play/pause your music. Swipe left and right to change tracks.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="six columns" style="line-height: 0;">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/buttons.png" alt="">
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	
	<!--
		HINTS
	-->
	<div class="row" style="color: #161616">
		<section style="padding-bottom: 10rem;">
			<div class="six columns padding-top-20">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-hints.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #a1a1a6">The shape around the bottom buttons is a clever detail to subtly hint at something more.</p>
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-intelligently-designed.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #a1a1a6">The scrubber (and buttons, if you like) stay on screen after scrolling. This allows you to control playback and read lyrics at the same time.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="six columns">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/hints.png" alt="">
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	<!--
		GESTURES
	-->
	<div class="row" style="color: white; background-color: #161616">
		<section style="margin-top: 5rem;">
			<div class="ten offset-by-one center columns">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-gestures.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem;">Gestures pack in more functionality without sacrificing screen space. However, they can be hard to find. In my design, gestures are an additional way to use the interface.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="twelve columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/gesture.png" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 5rem;">
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	<!--
		SIZES
	-->
	<div class="row">
		<div class="twelve columns center">
			<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/sizes.png" style="line-height: 0;" alt="">
		</div>	
	</div>
	
</body>
</html>